    <text id="B0258T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>This document is Paul's copy of a contract in which William Walker hired his son
                    out to a D. Newton VanLear for the period of one year.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="contract" id="d5">
                

               

                <p>Agreement made this day between <abbr expan="William">W<hi rend="underline">
                            <hi rend="super">m</hi>
                        </hi></abbr> Walker and D. N. VanLear, witnesseth that said Walker (<abbr
                        expan="colored">cold</abbr>) has this day hired to said VanLear his son
                    Governor to live with and labor for, and be subject entirely to the control of
                        <abbr expan="said">sd</abbr> VanLear until the 25th of December 1867. In
                    consideration of whose Services the said VanLear agrees to pay to said <abbr
                        expan="William">Wm.</abbr> Walker or his order the sum of Sixty Dollars and
                    to have the said sons clothes washed.</p>

                <p>Witnesseth our hands this the 4th January 1867</p>

                <p>Signed <abbr expan="William">Wm</abbr>
                    <add hand="h1" place="inline">his mark</add> X Walker<lb/>D. N. VanLear</p>

                <p><abbr expan="Testified">Test</abbr> F. D. Dillinger</p>

                <p>This is to certify that the above is a true copy of an article in my hands
                    between <abbr expan="William">Wm</abbr> Walker <abbr expan="colored">cold</abbr>
                    &amp; D. Newton VanLear, May 11th 1867.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>S. Paul</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Date of agreement between VanLear &amp; Walker Jany
                        4/67 3 months &amp; 18 days according to Walkers statement.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
